gomodel:SYNGO_357  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Using both confocal microscopy and superresolution STED microscopy, is demonstrated that DSyd-1 is present at the presynaptic active zone of the drosophila neuromuscular junction.\n\nDSyd-1 closely colocalized with BRP a well established marker of the active zone (Figure 2D, 3). Dsyd-1 staining was reminiscent of the staining pattern of DLiprin, another constituent of the active zone (Figure 3).\n\nA knockout control is provided for the DSyd-1 antibody.\n\nThe mammalian gene mSYD1A might also be present at synapses (Wentzel 2013) but currently available data are not sufficient to prove this.. Experimental description: Genetics. Fly strains were reared under standard laboratory conditions (Sigrist et al.,\n2003)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2017-08-31" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_357" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_7227" .
